            <title><![CDATA[Xbox Consoles And Games Get A Price Hike, Borderlands 4 Gets A Showcase, And More Of The Week's Top Stories]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/polygon-sold-giant-bomb-xbox-price-borderlands-4-1851778862</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/xbox-consoles-and-games-get-a-price-hike-borderlands-4-gets-a-showcase-and-more-of-the-weeks-top-stories.1180377/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/polygon-sold-giant-bomb-xbox-price-borderlands-4-1851778862<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="efa978d036416fb996cf7b532431ed6d" data-recommend-id="image://efa978d036416fb996cf7b532431ed6d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Vox Media<!-- -->, <!-- -->Giant Bomb / Fandom<!-- -->, <!-- -->Halo Studios<!-- -->, <!-- -->Microsoft / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Gearbox / 2K / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Lucasfilm / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="efa978d036416fb996cf7b532431ed6d" data-recommend-id="image://efa978d036416fb996cf7b532431ed6d" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>This week saw gaming website <em>Polygon </em>sold to Valnet, the company that owns <em>Screen Rant</em> and <em>Game Rant </em>among other sites, and many of its staffers laid off. Meanwhile publication at another gaming site, <em>Giant Bomb</em>,  is currently on hold as owner Fandom engages in what it calls a “strategic reset and realignment of our media brands” and some staffers suggest the company has interfered with the site’s content and its famously irreverent tone. </p><p>Elsewhere, Microsoft announced that Xbox consoles were going up in price, effective immediately, and that by this holiday season, we can expect higher prices on Xbox games as well. And we got a closer look at <em>Borderlands 4</em>&nbsp;via a new PlayStation State of Play presentation. Read on for all the details on these stories and more.</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7b7e3de78102ad34be1539f5539bfefe" data-recommend-id="image://7b7e3de78102ad34be1539f5539bfefe" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A logo shows the word polygon. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A logo shows the word polygon. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Vox Media</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7b7e3de78102ad34be1539f5539bfefe" data-recommend-id="image://7b7e3de78102ad34be1539f5539bfefe" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A logo shows the word polygon. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The video game website <em>Polygon</em> has been sold to click-farm powerhouse Valnet and much of its masthead has been laid off, <em>Kotaku</em> has learned. The sale was subsequently <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20250501630767/en/Valnet-Acquires-Premium-Gaming-Publication-Polygon-from-Vox-Media&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20250501630767/en/Valnet-Acquires-Premium-Gaming-Publication-Polygon-from-Vox-Media" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">announced in a press release</a></span>. Multiple staff members have posted online about losing their jobs or about colleagues now being out of work.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/polygon-sold-vox-media-valnet-layoffs-digital-gaming-1851778655?_gl=1*5t6jdo*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NjE4MjQ5NC42My4xLjE3NDYyMDYyNDkuMzEuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/polygon-sold-vox-media-valnet-layoffs-digital-gaming-1851778655?_gl=1*5t6jdo*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NjE4MjQ5NC42My4xLjE3NDYyMDYyNDkuMzEuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="26f9d5bf5170d56963c36415887ef4b6" data-recommend-id="image://26f9d5bf5170d56963c36415887ef4b6" data-format="png" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A logo reads &quot;Giant Bomb.&quot; " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A logo reads &quot;Giant Bomb.&quot; " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Giant Bomb / Fandom</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="26f9d5bf5170d56963c36415887ef4b6" data-recommend-id="image://26f9d5bf5170d56963c36415887ef4b6" data-format="png" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A logo reads &quot;Giant Bomb.&quot; " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Giant Bomb</em>’s future is uncertain following a showdown with parent company Fandom, which also owns <em>GameSpot</em>, over editorial interference. Creative director Dan Ryckert announced on a recent livestream that he would no longer be appearing on the Giant Bombcast and co-host Jeff Grubb confirmed on social media on Thursday that he’s no longer with the company.<em> Giant Bomb</em> content is currently on hold while Fandom engages in a “strategic reset and realignment of our media brands,” it confirmed to <em>Kotaku</em>.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/giant-bomb-fandom-dan-ryckert-jeff-grubb-gerstmann-1851778728?_gl=1*1vgsdej*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NjE4MjQ5NC42My4xLjE3NDYyMDYyNDkuMzEuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/giant-bomb-fandom-dan-ryckert-jeff-grubb-gerstmann-1851778728?_gl=1*1vgsdej*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NjE4MjQ5NC42My4xLjE3NDYyMDYyNDkuMzEuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="65d1d650b2bd64ccdfca87212957b046" data-recommend-id="image://65d1d650b2bd64ccdfca87212957b046" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Xboxes with red pointy up arrows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Xboxes with red pointy up arrows." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Microsoft / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="65d1d650b2bd64ccdfca87212957b046" data-recommend-id="image://65d1d650b2bd64ccdfca87212957b046" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Xboxes with red pointy up arrows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://support.xbox.com/en-US/help/hardware-network/console/may-2025-pricing-updates&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://support.xbox.com/en-US/help/hardware-network/console/may-2025-pricing-updates" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft has announced</a></span> it will be raising the prices of all Xbox consoles, accessories, and games, and the increases are <em>huge</em>. Console and peripheral prices will go up today, May 1, by an enormous amount, while new first-party game prices will all hit $80 by the holidays. - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/microsoft-xbox-series-x-s-price-increase-may-2025-1851778615&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/microsoft-xbox-series-x-s-price-increase-may-2025-1851778615">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1f5b5deecb76f5a078127083871f6872" data-recommend-id="image://1f5b5deecb76f5a078127083871f6872" data-format="png" data-width="1024" data-height="574" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo Switch hangs in the air. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Nintendo Switch hangs in the air. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1f5b5deecb76f5a078127083871f6872" data-recommend-id="image://1f5b5deecb76f5a078127083871f6872" data-format="png" data-width="1024" data-height="574" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo Switch hangs in the air. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p> The Nintendo Switch received a major firmware update today that paves the way for its integration with the Switch 2 and institutes a less than stellar new regime of virtual game sharing. But firmware version 20.0.0 also made some other equally notable but less advertised changes, including a major shift to how Nintendo ranks best-selling games in the eShop. The result could have big ramifications for how games are discovered on one of the biggest console install-bases in history, and could help alleviate <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-eshop-switch-slop-clones-unpacking-scam-ai-art-1851722248&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-eshop-switch-slop-clones-unpacking-scam-ai-art-1851722248">some of the platform’s “slop” problem</a></span>.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/slop-nintendo-switch-eshop-best-seller-firmware-update-1851778523&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/slop-nintendo-switch-eshop-best-seller-firmware-update-1851778523">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2797b124069af2d1edbf35fee5ca0fc2" data-recommend-id="image://2797b124069af2d1edbf35fee5ca0fc2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Gearbox / 2K / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2797b124069af2d1edbf35fee5ca0fc2" data-recommend-id="image://2797b124069af2d1edbf35fee5ca0fc2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Today, we learned a lot more about <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/borderlands-4-release-date-state-play-gta-6-fall-2025-1851762044&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/borderlands-4-release-date-state-play-gta-6-fall-2025-1851762044"><em>Borderlands 4</em></a></span> during a roughly 20-minute PlayStation State of Play dedicated exclusively to Gearbox and 2K’s upcoming sci-fi looter shooter sequel. - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/borderlands-4-state-of-play-gearbox-round-up-trailer-1851778578&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/borderlands-4-state-of-play-gearbox-round-up-trailer-1851778578">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4f00681faf5577f2403cb4bf972ee737" data-recommend-id="image://4f00681faf5577f2403cb4bf972ee737" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Lucasfilm / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4f00681faf5577f2403cb4bf972ee737" data-recommend-id="image://4f00681faf5577f2403cb4bf972ee737" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>A greatest hits collection of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-best-games-ranked-jedi-knight-dark-forces-lis-1848893189?_gl=1*1iw9k22*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NTg1MTc4Ni4zMzYuMS4xNzQ1ODUzNzQ0LjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-best-games-ranked-jedi-knight-dark-forces-lis-1848893189?_gl=1*1iw9k22*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0NTg1MTc4Ni4zMzYuMS4xNzQ1ODUzNzQ0LjkuMC4w"><em>Star Wars</em> PC games</a></span> are currently on sale right now on GOG, just a few days ahead of May the 4th. And some are now part of an awesome <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gog-games-preservation-program-drm-1851696363&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gog-games-preservation-program-drm-1851696363">preservation program</a></span> that will help keep them playable for years to come.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-games-may-4th-sale-gog-preservation-pc-deals-1851778109&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-games-may-4th-sale-gog-preservation-pc-deals-1851778109">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="33836f5190052218946100376b8d7678" data-recommend-id="image://33836f5190052218946100376b8d7678" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Miis prepare to share games on their Switches. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Miis prepare to share games on their Switches. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="33836f5190052218946100376b8d7678" data-recommend-id="image://33836f5190052218946100376b8d7678" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Miis prepare to share games on their Switches. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-march-27-2025-metroid-pokemon-dragon-qu-1851772682&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-march-27-2025-metroid-pokemon-dragon-qu-1851772682">Nintendo Switch</a></span> just got a major update to prepare for the arrival of Switch 2 in June. Ver. 20.0.0, released overnight, adds system transfers to Switch 2 as well as support for the new console’s GameShare feature and the sharing of virtual game cards. Players have quickly discovered a major caveat for that last part: when using virtual game cards, you can’t simultaneously play a game online across two separate Switches. It’s a confusing hang-up with significant consequences.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-share-virtual-game-card-firmware-20-0-1851778447&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-share-virtual-game-card-firmware-20-0-1851778447">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
